					<div class="col-xl-8 col-lg-8">
						<div class="services-details__content">
							<img src="images/background/customer-service.jpeg" alt="globextechnology" />
							<h2 class="mt-4" style="font-size: 36px;">CSR Services</h2>
							<p>CS services refer to the various channels and methods that companies use to provide
								customer support and assistance. Effective customer service services content should be
								tailored to the specific channel or method of communication being used. Here are some
								tips for creating effective customer service content for different service channels:</p>

							<ul>
								<li><span>Phone support:</span>Be polite and attentive, listen actively to the customer,
									and use a clear and concise tone to convey information.</li>
								<li><span>Email support:</span>Use clear and direct language to provide detailed answers
									to customer inquiries or issues.

								</li>
								<li><span> Live chat support:</span> Respond quickly and professionally, use a friendly
									and engaging tone, and provide relevant links or resources to help the customer.
								</li>
								<li><span>Social media support: </span> Respond promptly to customer inquiries or issues
									on social media platforms, use a friendly and approachable tone, and provide helpful
									resources or links to address their concerns.</li>
								<li><span>In-person support:</span>Greet customers warmly, actively listen to their
									concerns, and provide clear and concise information to address their needs.</li>
							</ul>
							<p>Regardless of the channel being used, effective customer service content should aim to be
								helpful, informative, and courteous. It should provide accurate information, practical
								solutions, and a positive experience for the customer. By providing exceptional customer
								service content across different service channels, you can build strong relationships
								with your customers and ensure their satisfaction with your products and services.</p>
							<h3>CSR responsibilities</h3>
							<p>As a customer service representative for a software company, your goal is to help
								customers with their technical inquiries and issues. Here are some tips for creating
								effective customer service content as a representative for a software company:

							</p>
							<ul>
								<li><span> Understand the software:</span>Gain a thorough understanding of the software
									that your company offers, including its features and functionalities.</li>
								<li><span>Use technical language: </span>Use technical language to explain complex
									concepts and issues to customers.</li>
								<li><span> Offer practical solutions: </span>Provide practical and actionable solutions
									to customers' technical problems.</li>
								<li><span>Use screenshots or videos:</span>Use screenshots or videos to visually
									demonstrate how to use certain features or solve particular issues.</li>
								<li><span>Offer self-help resources:</span>Provide customers with self-help resources,
									such as FAQs, user manuals, and tutorials to help them troubleshoot issues on their
									own.</li>
								<li><span>Follow up: </span>Follow up with customers after their issue has been resolved
									to ensure their satisfaction and address any additional concerns.</li>
								<li><span>Be professional:</span>Maintain a professional tone and demeanor, even in
									difficult situations.

								</li>
								<li><span>Continuously update your knowledge: </span>Stay up-to-date with the latest
									software updates, industry trends, and customer needs by continuously updating your
									knowledge and skills.</li>
							</ul>



						</div>
